snippet.textDisplay:
All parties were at fault here. However, the guy from new Delhi has no idea about what he's talking about. 

Victoria and tennis Australia do not grant visas to enter the country. Victoria is a state, and tennis Australia is an association. Novak had to fullfil the reuqirments of the country. Unfortunately tennis Australia facilitated the visa, which has also thrown a spanner in the works on what the govt had advised vs the interpretation . There's a lot more, but everyone at the end is all at fault for the mix-up. 

One thing Novak could've done is not challenge the findings, he pushed it and the govt faught back. And now is possibly facing a 3 year ban (which is probably unlikely upheld - he'll probably request a waiver next year and it would be granted most likely). But regardless, I wonder why his legal team, and his team of advisors led him down this path.

Well we now konw why the term "KANGAROO COURT" comes from Australia. Why do they call it a kangaroo court?
Ostensibly, the term comes from the notion of justice proceeding "by leaps", like a kangaroo – in other words, "jumping over" (intentionally ignoring) evidence that would be in favour of the defendant.

snippet.textDisplay:
Medical ethics:
1) Informed consent -- the right to say no without paperwork!
2) Patient Autonomy - my body, MY CHOICE - the right to say no without paperwork!
3) Non-maleficence -- FIRST, do no harm!
4) Beneficence -- do good.  The reason this is #4 on the list (and there are more than 4 ethics) is so that we DO NOT have what is happening now which is paternalism where someone else is telling you what they believe is good for you!

Stand for medical freedom!  Stand for medical ethics!  NO MANDATES!!!!

A) Unvaccinated does not equal infected
B) Since NONE of the vaccines prevents infection or infecting others, being vaccinated does not equal being safe!
